critical_positive: In general, the exchange was fairly balanced. Initially, she asked a lot of general and good, open-ended questions.  I feel I responded well and then she returned the response. It was a pleasant experience overall. There wasn't a lot of silence and we were able to talk about things that are either relevant to us or overall interesting topics.
critical_negative: Although I stated earlier that the exchange was overall balanced and I still maintain that to be true, I feel that some of her answers were a little short. Maybe I talked too much or I don't know. Although she was carrying the conversation and she came up with the questions, I feel that her answers to the questions were a little less revealing.

rest_of_day_open: I think the rest of my week will be boring.  I haven't been out much since coronavirus and I haven't seen any of my friends.  I have enough food and drink that I don't need to leave my house.  I will watch TV and stay in my bed all weekend.
critical_positive: The conversation worked well because we were both originally from Europe and we had both married American people.  He was impressed I could say two words in his mother tongue because not many people know it.  We were both in New York City and he was familiar with the area I lived in.
critical_negative: I didn't feel like there was enough variation in conversation.  I feel like I was waiting for a moment to interject.  I think he thought he was being helpful listing off a bunch of survey sites he uses for me, so I could sign up to them too, but I was just bored.
